(925, 1, '2015-12-16 18:02:43', '2015-12-16 18:02:43', '<p class="journal-inner"><span class="drop-cap">A</span>fter an off-road wine filled trip through the Chianti region of Italy (think Napa valley with hand made signs and no paved roads), the next GPS way point was set to the port city of Porto Venere; a small city on the north west side of the “boot”.  Arriving in a tiny, but very “efficient”, cinquecento covered in Tuscan sand and dirt, I handed the Fiat to the valet driver whose skill is akin to fitting the square peg in the round hole.I digress. Porto Venere is a place where no car is desired because it can be walked in a matter of hours, a port city where you actually connect with a local crowd. Absent and drowned of heavy tourism and loud noises, the multicolor hand painted buildings touch the sea wall.  I was captured immediately and thrilled to be spending the weekend. I walked aimlessly with my trusted partner *#TBT film Leica M6* and captured as much as I could.  They say (<del>read Wikipedia</del>) the name, Portovenere, comes from the goddess Venus where the church of Peter the Apostle now stands.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-907" src="http://dev.hungrylemur.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/IMG_1961-2000x2000.jpg" alt="Processed with VSCOcam with n1 preset" width="2000" height="2000" />\r\n\r\nWalking up to the church is an adventure and has some great detours (hint: bring your swimwear).  Just before reaching the top, you can go to the rock formed beach and just relax on one of the ledges or have a very adventures (and cold) swim.  All jokes aside, the views are spectacular. The rock formations in the middle of the ocean, the natural caves, and beautiful clear water make it the spot for locals to go and just <em>chill</em>. Picture this; a simple church laid out in black and white stone with only natural light bouncing its true beauty and simplicity.\r\n\r\nIt left me with a final thought: When I have a daughter, she will be married here*', 'THE HIDDEN "6th" LAND', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '888-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-16 18:02:43', '2015-12-16 18:02:43', '', 888, 'http://dev.hungrylemur.com/888-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(268, 1, '2015-09-21 08:25:40', '2015-09-21 08:25:40', 'INITIATIVE\r\n\r\n“Momma said: There is only so much fortune a man really needs- and the rest is for showin’ off”-\r\n\r\nForrest Gump\r\n\r\nWe are a small company. Fueled by a few creative individuals who want to procure beautiful eyewear in a way that hasn’t been done before.\r\n\r\nWe believe in having a sustainable business, with a portion set aside to effect whatever change is within our reach. Our ambition is not to constantly reshape the bottom line and increase profits; but to effect change in our industry with out work and outside of it with our initiative.\r\n\r\nYour one pair of DIROCCO’s helps restore the sight of one person who has become blind through cataracts. So enjoy your DIROCCO’s and thank you for helping us restore the gift of sight.', 'Warranty', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '146-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-21 08:25:40', '2015-09-21 08:25:40', '', 146, 'http://dev.hungrylemur.com/146-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
